topIssues.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**

It's frustrating when you load up a chat after a reboot (or other downtime) and having to type out the previous chat again.

**Describe the solution you'd like**

Add a resend chat button to the context of previous chats from the user (near the delete button). This would allow the user to easily resend the same message again.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**

Copying and pasting the previous text works, but is slow and tedious.

**Additional context**

elizaos: `v1.0.4`

topIssues.title: MessageBusService: Agent not a participant in channel {channelId}, ignoring message
topIssues.author: exitsimulation
topIssues.body:
**Describe the bug**

I am trying to send messages through the API using postman. The message goes through

POST /messages
```
{
  "entityId": "b8af647b-f617-0ae3-ab07-acb81861d7e2",
  "roomId": "46bf60b4-cfa4-4ec4-a9f3-db1ec9ab0aa1",
  "channelId": "89591c0f-7b20-45a0-9266-56a6ce68de13",
  "serverId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "text": "Test Message!",
  "source": "postman"
}
```

Response:
```
{
    "success": true,
    "data": {
        "message": "Message submitted to central store. Target agent b8af647b-f617-0ae3-ab07-acb81861d7e2 will process it.",
        "messageId": "11346cd8-46f2-4a7e-ae71-b6e72ee865ee",
        "targetAgentId": "b8af647b-f617-0ae3-ab07-acb81861d7e2",
        "submittedChannelId": "89591c0f-7b20-45a0-9266-56a6ce68de13"
    }
}
```

However in the logs it says `[test-agent] MessageBusService: Agent not a participant in channel 89591c0f-7b20-45a0-9266-56a6ce68de13, ignoring message`

The strange thing is that I am already running a setup routine through a custom plugin to set a channel, room and add the agent as participant on this channel. See here:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fe11e37b-0925-4498-a3a2-0985c70151ab)


After running this I am inspecting the live database and the channel_participants relation is there:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d5524f18-31e9-46bb-983e-3973c7140c44)

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/18921312-949d-47b2-83e3-73cc663fce73)

**Theory**: 
MessageBusService seems to access stale data in regards to channel participants.

Is there any way to fix this?

topPRs.title: Fix/realtime-message-deletion
topPRs.author: standujar
topPRs.body:
# Risks

**Medium** - Changes to SocketIO event handling and API routing
- Could affect message synchronization across clients
- Routing changes might impact plugin functionality
- Client-side state management modifications

# Background

## What does this PR do?

- Add messageDeleted and channelCleared SocketIO events
- Implement client-side handlers for real-time UI updates  
- Fix routing to exclude /api/messages/ from plugin handler
- Add DELETE /central-channels/:channelId endpoint
- Clean up debug logs and improve TypeScript types
- Prevent 404 errors when deleting channels

Fixes message deletion requiring page refresh

## What kind of change is this?

**Bug fixes** (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
**Improvements** (misc. changes to existing features)

## Why are we doing this? Any context or related work?

Users experienced poor UX where deleted messages remained visible in the chat interface until manually refreshing the page. The DELETE API worked correctly but the UI wasn't receiving real-time updates via SocketIO events.

# Documentation changes needed?

My changes do not require a change to the project documentation.

# Testing

## Where should a reviewer start?

1. Review SocketIO event handling in `socketio-manager.ts` and `use-socket-chat.ts`
2. Check routing exclusion logic in `eliza/packages/cli/src/server/api/index.ts`
3. Verify new DELETE endpoint in `messages.ts`

## Detailed testing steps

- Start an agent and open the chat interface
- Send several messages in a DM or group chat
- Delete a message using the delete button
  - Verify message disappears immediately without page refresh
  - Verify SocketIO `messageDeleted` event is received
- Clear entire channel using clear button
  - Verify all messages disappear immediately
  - Verify SocketIO `channelCleared` event is received
- Delete a DM channel entirely
  - Verify no 404 errors occur
  - Verify proper API response

## Screenshots

### Before
- Messages remained visible after deletion until page refresh
- 404 errors when deleting channels
- Verbose debug logs with emojis

### After  
- Messages disappear instantly upon deletion
- Clean channel deletion without errors
- Cleaner log output
- Real-time UI updates via SocketIO events

# Deploy Notes

## Database changes
None - only UI and API routing changes

## Deployment instructions
Standard build and restart required:
```bash
cd eliza
bun run build:client && bun run build:cli
```
Then restart the agent process.

topPRs.title: refactor: Enhance create command with TEE support and improved logic
topPRs.author: yungalgo
topPRs.body:
**Problem**

The elizaos create command was becoming cluttered and lacked a unified structure for handling different types of project creation (projects, plugins, agents). Also I found it unintuitive to pass -tee as a flag for project to clone the tee project instead of just having tee as a type. Also, there is stuff that is passing an ignore file in a string but it is already cloned over from the project starter and plugin starter and project tee starter templates.

**Solution**

Unified Type Selection: Instead of separate flags like --tee, the command now uses a single -t, --type option to select the creation type (project, plugin, agent, or tee). This simplifies the command's public API.
TEE Project Scaffolding: Adds a new project-tee-starter template and the logic required to create a new TEE-enabled project.
Refactored Logic: The internal logic has been broken down into smaller, single-responsibility functions (e.g., createProject, createPlugin, createAgent, createTEEProject), making the code easier to read, test, and maintain.
Improved Validation: Centralized and improved validation for project names and target directories to provide clearer error messages to the user.
Documentation Update: The CLI README.md and docs have been updated to reflect the new command structure and options.

**Details**

packages/cli/src/commands/create.ts: Completely overhauled to support the new type-based creation flow.
packages/project-tee-starter/: A new template package has been added for TEE projects.
packages/cli/README.md & packages/docs/docs/cli/create.md: Updated to document the new functionality.

Dependency Bumps: Updated @vitest/coverage-v8 in starter templates for consistency and removing of warning flash during creation

<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

## Summary by CodeRabbit

- **New Features**
  - Added support for creating TEE (Trusted Execution Environment) projects via the CLI, with dedicated prompts, templates, and instructions.

- **Documentation**
  - Updated CLI documentation to reflect the new TEE project type and revised usage examples.
  - Improved clarity and formatting in CLI and project creation documentation.

- **Chores**
  - Updated the @vitest/coverage-v8 development dependency to version 3.1.4 in project templates.

#### 1. **Responsive Character Form Buttons** ‚ú®
- **Container-aware responsiveness**: Replaced viewport-based breakpoints with actual container width detection

- **ResizeObserver integration**: Uses modern browser API for real-time container width monitoring
- **Comprehensive tooltips**: All form buttons now include helpful tooltips for better accessibility
- **Improved UX**: Buttons adapt to their actual context rather than just viewport size

#### 2. **Chat Interface Redesign** üí¨

**New Features:**

- Comprehensive tooltip system for all form buttons

### üéØ Benefits
- ‚úÖ **Better space utilization**: Components adapt to actual available space
- ‚úÖ **Consistent design language**: Unified styling across components

#### Character Form Enhancements:

#### Chat Interface Updates:

### üß™ Testing

- ‚úÖ Verified responsive behavior in various screen dimensions

This enhancement provides a significantly better user experience by making components truly responsive to their environment while maintaining consistency and accessibility across the entire interface. The implementation is performant, follows React best practices, and provides comprehensive user guidance through tooltips and improved visual feedback.
